[{"location":"benchmarks/#Performance-Benchmarks","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Performance Benchmarks","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"This page contains performance benchmarks comparing FFTA.jl against FFTW.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Interactive-Benchmark-Report","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Interactive Benchmark Report","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"<style>\n.benchmark-note {\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    padding: 15px;\n    border-left: 4px solid #3498db;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    background-color: rgba(52, 152, 219, 0.1);\n}\n.benchmark-warning {\n    padding: 20px;\n    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 193, 7, 0.5);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    background-color: rgba(255, 193, 7, 0.1);\n}\n@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {\n    .benchmark-note {\n        background-color: rgba(52, 152, 219, 0.15);\n        border-left-color: #5dade2;\n    }\n    .benchmark-warning {\n        background-color: rgba(255, 193, 7, 0.15);\n        border-color: rgba(255, 193, 7, 0.6);\n    }\n}\n</style>\n<div class=\"benchmark-note\">\n    <p><strong>Note:</strong> The interactive benchmark report below is generated automatically by the CI pipeline when benchmarks are run.</p>\n    <p>If you don't see the report, it means benchmarks haven't been run yet for this version of the documentation.</p>\n</div>","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"<div id=\"benchmark-container\">\n    <iframe src=\"../assets/benchmarks/benchmark_report.html\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 2000px; border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 4px;\" onload=\"this.style.height=(this.contentWindow.document.body.scrollHeight+50)+'px';\">\n        <p>Your browser does not support iframes. <a href=\"../assets/benchmarks/benchmark_report.html\">Click here to view the benchmark report</a>.</p>\n    </iframe>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n// Check if benchmark report exists\nfetch('../assets/benchmarks/benchmark_report.html')\n    .then(response => {\n        if (!response.ok) {\n            document.getElementById('benchmark-container').innerHTML =\n                '<div class=\"benchmark-warning\">' +\n                '<h3>⚠️ Benchmark Report Not Available</h3>' +\n                '<p>The benchmark report has not been generated yet. Benchmarks are automatically run on:</p>' +\n                '<ul>' +\n                '<li>Pull requests that modify source code</li>' +\n                '<li>Pushes to the main branch</li>' +\n                '<li>Manual workflow dispatch</li>' +\n                '</ul>' +\n                '<p>To generate benchmarks locally, run:</p>' +\n                '<pre><code>cd benchmark\\njulia run_benchmarks.jl</code></pre>' +\n                '</div>';\n        }\n    })\n    .catch(error => {\n        document.getElementById('benchmark-container').innerHTML =\n            '<div class=\"benchmark-warning\">' +\n            '<h3>⚠️ Benchmark Report Not Available</h3>' +\n            '<p>The benchmark report could not be loaded.</p>' +\n            '</div>';\n    });\n</script>","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Running-Benchmarks-Locally","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Running Benchmarks Locally","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"To run the benchmarks on your local machine:","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"cd benchmark\njulia run_benchmarks.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"This will:","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"Run FFTA benchmarks in an isolated environment\nRun FFTW benchmarks in an isolated environment\nGenerate an interactive HTML report at benchmark/benchmark_report.html","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"For more details, see the benchmark README.","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Benchmark-Methodology","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmark Methodology","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"The benchmark suite compares FFTA.jl (a pure Julia FFT implementation) against FFTW.jl (Julia bindings to the FFTW C library).","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Array-Size-Categories","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Array Size Categories","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"Benchmarks are organized into categories based on array size structure:","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"Odd Powers of 2: 2¹, 2³, 2⁵, ..., 2¹⁵ (2, 8, 32, 128, 512, 2048, 8192, 32768)\nEven Powers of 2: 2², 2⁴, 2⁶, ..., 2¹⁴ (4, 16, 64, 256, 1024, 4096, 16384)\nPowers of 3: 3¹, 3², 3³, ..., 3⁹ (3, 9, 27, 81, 243, 729, 2187, 6561, 19683)\nComposite: 3, 12, 60, 300, 2100, 23100 (cumulative products of 3, 4, 5, 5, 7, 11)\nPrime Numbers: 20 logarithmically-spaced primes up to 20,000","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Metrics","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Metrics","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"For each array size, we measure:","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"Median time: Median execution time across 100 samples\nRuntime/N: Runtime divided by array length (shows scaling efficiency)\nMean/Min/Max time: Statistical measures of performance","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Isolation","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Isolation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"Each package is benchmarked in a completely separate Julia process to ensure:","category":"page"},{"location":"benchmarks/","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"FFTW doesn't take precedence over FFTA when both are loaded\nFair and accurate performance comparison\nNo cross-contamination between implementations","category":"page"},{"location":"dev/#Development-Documentation","page":"Development Tools","title":"Development Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"dev/","page":"Development Tools","title":"Development Tools","text":"Here is the documentation for key parts of the development side of the package.","category":"page"},{"location":"dev/","page":"Development Tools","title":"Development Tools","text":"CallGraphNode\nCallGraph\nCallGraphNode!\nfft!\nfft_dft!\nfft_pow2!\nfft_pow3!\nfft_pow4!","category":"page"},{"location":"#FFTA.jl","page":"FFTA.jl","title":"FFTA.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"FFTA.jl","title":"FFTA.jl","text":"Documentation for FFTA.jl","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"FFTA.jl","title":"FFTA.jl","text":"fft\nbfft","category":"page"}]
